
u2_anon  is a tool that allows you to "share" anonymized unified2
files to help debug issues or share results without compromising 
the information contained inside.

https://github.com/binf/u2_anon


Installation:

32 bit
dpkg -i u2-anon_0.9.0b-1_i386.deb


64 bit
dpkg -i u2-anon_0.9.0b-1_amd64.deb

Usage:

# u2_anon
----------------------------------------------
|       Unified2 Anonymizer usage()          |
----------------------------------------------
| -r:   [Unified2 Input file (single)]
| -o:   [Unified2 Output File (single)]
| -R:   [Unified2 Input Directory]
| -O:   [Unified2 Output Directory]
| -s:   [Unified2 File Prefix]
| -eE:  [Anonymize Event]
| -lL:  [Anonymize LinkLayer (ethernet)]
| -pP:  [Anonymize Packet data]
| -xX:  [Anonymize Extra DATA event]
| -v:   [Verbose flag]
| -h:   [Show Usage]
----------------------------------------------

To anonymize a sigle file:

u2_anon -e  -r Unified2_Input_file -o Unified2_Output_File
